line.comment: * If follower ships should also jump, iniciate jump on all follower ships of THIS ship with the same priority this script is running
* Check, whether we are docked at target, or at same asset as target
* Undock; break operation, if still not in space after trying to undock (happens if e.g. a fighter is docked at a frigate, and the firgate is docked at some station)
* Let's try to jump to target; done in a while loop to prevent being stuck a sector of an object just about to jump to another sector. Explanation below
* THIS is currently in sector A, is to jump to object being in sector B, but object just wants to jump to sector C
* THIS iniciates jumping to sector B, in the meantime, oject jumps to sector C
* THIS arrives in B, but object is already in C -> without a while loop, THIS will now fly to sector C, though THIS could easily jump again
